Sentece: The method showed good agreement of results (n=15): inaccuracy (5.6%), intra- and inter-day variability (1.1% and 3.9%, respectively), recovery (94.9%), limit of detection (0.8 μg/mL), lower limit of quantitation (1.6 μg/mL) and acceptable stability over 24 h in the auto-sampler.
Title: A high-performance liquid chromatographic method for benznidazole quantitation in plasma of patients with Chagas disease.
